2.2 Communication Protocols Between Modules

Internal Communication Matrix:

Sender → Receiver Communication Protocol Purpose Example
Michael → Gabriel SECURITY_BREACH_ALERT Inform communication layer about threats for user notification "DDoS attack detected, informing users of service degradation"
Michael → Raphael RESOURCE_CONSTRAINT Signal need for optimization due to security constraints "Encryption overhead causing latency, request load balancing"
Gabriel → Michael USER_INTENT_ANALYSIS Provide threat intelligence from user interactions "Multiple users reporting phishing attempts from domain X"
Gabriel → Raphael USER_FEEDBACK_STREAM Channel user sentiment for system optimization "Users expressing confusion about feature Y, suggest UI simplification"
Raphael → Michael SYSTEM_HEALTH_REPORT Identify vulnerabilities from performance patterns "Server cluster 3 showing abnormal I/O patterns, possible compromise"
Raphael → Gabriel OPTIMIZATION_REPORT Explain system changes to communication layer "Database indexed for 40% faster queries, update user documentation"

