VI. CHALLENGES & MITIGATION STRATEGIES

6.1 Technical Challenges

Challenge Description Mitigation Strategy
Cognitive Load Modules overwhelming each other with alerts Implement priority queuing with cross-module validation
Contradictory Goals Security vs. Usability vs. Performance Dynamic constraint satisfaction algorithms
Single Point of Failure Orchestrator becomes bottleneck Federated Triad architecture with consensus protocols
Training Data Bias Modules develop conflicting worldviews Shared base training with specialized fine-tuning

6.2 Ethical & Governance Challenges

The Triad Governance Framework:

· Michael's Ethical Constraint: "Thou shalt not protect the system by deceiving its users"
· Gabriel's Ethical Constraint: "Thou shalt not communicate with clarity while obscuring truth"
· Raphael's Ethical Constraint: "Thou shalt not optimize for efficiency at the cost of equity"

Transparency Implementation:

```yaml
triad_governance:
  decision_logging:
    required: true
    retention_period: 7_years
    access_control: regulated_auditors
  
  conflict_resolution:
    primary: human_oversight_board
    secondary: constitutional_ai_constraints
    fallback: system_safe_mode
  
  bias_monitoring:
    michael: fairness_in_enforcement
    gabriel: clarity_across_demographics  
    raphael: equitable_optimization
```

